ADOPTED SENATE
A RESOLUTION
1 Commending Kelly Loeffler; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Kelly Loeffler was appointed by the President of the United States to serve as
3 the Administrator of the Small Business Administration (SBA), bringing her record of public
4 service and leadership to the role; and
5 WHEREAS, Kelly Loeffler was raised on a farm in Illinois, where her family grew soybeans
6 and raised cattle, and she served in her local church and 4-H club prior to attending the
7 University of Illinois at Urbana Champaign to earn her bachelor's degree and DePaul
8 University for her Master of Business Administration; and
9 WHEREAS, Kelly Loeffler has previously served as a United States Senator from Georgia,
10 during which time she championed policies to support small businesses, strengthen the
11 economy, and empower American workers; and
12 WHEREAS, she further served as an advocate for tax reform, deregulation, and measures to
13 expand economic opportunities for communities around the country; and
