14 WHEREAS, Kelly Loeffler's dedication to public service is further demonstrated by her
15 commitment to promoting access to education, healthcare, and workforce development
16 initiatives that equip small business owners with the tools they need to succeed; and
17 WHEREAS, her leadership during the COVID-19 pandemic was instrumental in securing
18 critical support for small businesses through programs such as the Paycheck Protection
19 Program, which saved countless jobs and helped businesses remain operational; and
20 WHEREAS, Kelly Loeffler has consistently demonstrated a deep commitment to fiscal
21 responsibility, transparency, and accountability in government, earning the trust and respect
22 of her constituents.
23 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
24 commend Kelly Loeffler for her distinguished career, impactful tenure in the United States
25 Senate, and her ongoing efforts as the Administrator of the Small Business Administration
26 to strengthen and support American small businesses.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
28 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the public and the
29 press.
